com.bigdata.rdf.vocab

Interface VocabularyDecl

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseVocabularyDecl, BSBMVocabularyDecl, DCAllVocabularyDecl, DCElementsVocabularyDecl, FOAFVocabularyDecl, GeoSpatialVocabularyDecl, LUBMVocabularyDecl, OPVocabularyDecl, OWLVocabularyDecl, RDFSVocabularyDecl, RDFVocabularyDecl, SesameVocabularyDecl, SKOSVocabularyDecl, TestVocabularyDecl_BLZG1591, VoidVocabularyDecl, XMLSchemaVocabularyDecl

    public interface VocabularyDecl
    A class for declaring a Vocabulary.

    Note: Implementations of a VocabularyDecl MUST be stable across the life cycle of an AbstractTripleStore. For this reason it is strongly recommended that new versions of a vocabulary are defined in a new class.

    Each class SHOULD provide a declaration for the namespace(s) used by the vocabulary. It is convention to expose this String value as a public static field named NAMESPACE. Declaring the namespace used by provides for compact encoding of URIs within that namespace (e.g., using a VocabURIShortIV for the namespace and a compressed unicode representation of the localName of the URI) even if those URIs were not part of the original vocabulary declaration. Thus, it provides a compact fallback encoding if the vocabulary evolves after the AbstractTripleStore has been provisioned.
